ARINC 429 Encoder/Decoder Example
==================================================
Test Case: Encoding altitude data
Label 0o010 (octal 010) represents altitude data
Altitude value: 1000 feet

 Encoding Process
Input Parameters:
label =8, (octal) + 0o10 =8 decimal
 data =1000
 ssm  =0
 sdi  =0

Step 1 - Convert to binary:
  label 8 -> '00001000' (8 bits)
  label reversed -> '00010000' (ARINC 429 LSB first)
  data 1000 -> '0000000001111101000' (19 bits)
  ssm 0 -> '00' (2 bits)
  sdi 0 -> '00' (2 bits)

Step 2 - Combine fields:
  Combined (no parity): '0001000000000000011111010000000' (31 bits)
    Bits 1-8  (Label): '00010000'
    Bits 9-27 (Data):  '0000000001111101000'
    Bits 28-29 (SSM):  '00'
    Bits 30-31 (SDI):  '00'

Step 3 - Calculate parity:
  Number of 1s in first 31 bits: 7
  7 is odd
  For odd parity, need to add: '0'
  Final 32-bit word: '00010000000000000111110100000000'

Step 4 - Convert to integer:
  Binary: 0b10000000000000111110100000000
  Decimal: 268467456
  Hexadecimal: 0x10007d00

==================================================

=== DECODING PROCESS ===
Input: 268467456 (decimal) = 0x10007d00 (hex)
32-bit binary: '00010000000000000111110100000000'

Step 1 - Extract fields:
  Bits 1-8  (Label reversed): '00010000'
  Label normal order: '00001000' = 8 decimal = 0o10 octal
  Bits 9-27 (Data): '0000000001111101000' = 1000 decimal
  Bits 28-29 (SSM): '00' = 0 decimal
  Bits 30-31 (SDI): '00' = 0 decimal
  Bit 32 (Parity): '0' = 0 decimal

Step 2 - Verify parity:
  1s in first 31 bits: 7
  Expected parity: 0
  Actual parity: 0
  Parity valid: True

Decoded result: {'label': 8, 'data': 1000, 'ssm': 0, 'sdi': 0, 'parity': 0, 'parity_valid': True}

==================================================
SUMMARY:
Original input: label=0o10, data=1000
Encoded word: 268467456 (decimal), 0x10007d00 (hex)
Decoded output: label=0o10, data=1000
Round-trip successful: True
